SIMPLE: torque
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Torque
<hw>Torque</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>torques</ets>
a twisted neck chain, fr. <ets>torquere</ets> to twist.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A collar or neck chain, usually twisted, especially as
worn by ancient barbaric nations, as the Gauls, Germans, and
Britons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[L. <ets>torquere</ets> to twist.]</ety>
<fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>That which tends to produce torsion; a couple of
forces.</def> <rj><au>J. Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Phys. Science)</fld> <def>A turning or twisting;
tendency to turn, or cause to turn, about an axis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torqued</ent>⟦br⟧
